The file ECReflect.java attempt to mimic the functionality in the Jave 1.1. Reflection API. Functionality and names match wherever possible. The main discrepancies are some extensions to Class Class (that have been put into InspectableClass as static methods explicitly called using the class in question as first argument) and the classes ec.inspect.Null, ec.inspect.Short, and ec.inspect.Byte that mimic functionality of similarly named classes in the java.lang package.

This class is not public and can therefore cannot be used outside this package.
